<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES: this competition seriously.''
</P>
<P>
   ``It would have an amazing positive effect on the North
Hollywood community.''
</P>
<P>
   DreamWorks' proposed studio would have been the first motion
picture production studio built in Los Angeles since the 1930s.
</P>
<P>
   Glendale City Manager Jim Starbird said he hopes to build on the
relationship the city developed with DreamWorks when it built its
animation shop there three years ago, and will encourage the
company to utilize its entire campus or look at other potential
sites in the city.
</P>
<P>
   ``We'd like to see Glendale be their home if we can meet their
needs,'' Starbird said.
</P>
<P>
   DreamWorks has not yet started construction on what was to be
Phase 2 of its animation complex, which includes a 100,000- to
150,000-square-foot building. Unlike Playa Vista, the animation
complex project was approved quickly.
</P>
<P>
   Quaschnick said DreamWorks could always ask to change its plans
and to build more space.
</P>
<P>
   ``They could develop the site more intensely than they had
planned. Instead of building three stories, they could build four
or five stories.''
</P>
<P>
   Palmdale also is interested, and officials are talking to
developers about the idea of establishing studios, including those
with ties to DreamWorks, said Mayor Jim Ledford.
</P>
<P>
   ``Our philosophy is not to direct them to a particular site. We
let them tell us what sites they are interested in and work with
them to make that happen,'' he said.
</P>
