<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   GAY-MURDERS (San Francisco) _ Shasta County sheriff's deputies
have arrested two brothers, believed to be white supremacists, in
connection with the shooting deaths of a gay couple in their rural
home outside of Redding, Calif. By RAY DELGADO.
</P>
<P>
   SF-FERRIES (San Francisco) _ Environmentalists are withdrawing
their support for a plan to make San Francisco Bay home to the
world's largest ferry system after a study concluded the scheme
would cause more pollution than the car and bus traffic it was
designed to replace. By ANITA WADHWANI.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL (``t'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CONNECTICUT (Burlington, Conn.) _ Connecticut has a
contradictory public image, seen as a bland suburb of New York yet
regarded as a backwater of traditional Yankee stodginess. The true
flavor of Connecticut does not start to come through until you move
away from the New York area to New Haven and beyond. By JEANNE
LeBLANC and DON STACOM.
</P>
<P>
   MAINE (Portland, Me.) _ From its biggest cities like Portland,
to its smallest villages, like Bailey's Island, life in midcoast
Maine hasn't changed all that much over the years. Since the
mid-1800s, when ``rusticators'' began coming north to enjoy Maine's
bucolic summers, the state has been a place to take refuge from the
stress of everyday life. By DONNA MARSHALL.
</P>
<P>
   NEW-HAMPSHIRE (Conway, N.H.) _ The ``Kanc,'' a 34-mile scenic
highway, passes through thousands of acres of New Hampshire forest,
by scenic rivers and waterfalls, between Crawford and Franconia
Notches and by historic homes, inns and villages. The byway even
leads to the grand old Mount Washington Hotel and the coal-fired
Cog Railway locomotive that belches black smoke as it chugs up the
mountain. By FRED STETSON.
</P>
<P>
   RHODE-ISLAND (Misquamicut, R.I.) _ Rhode Island may be the
smallest state in the union, but its breathtaking ocean views, vast
stretches of sandy beaches, elegant mansions and world-class music
festivals make it a big vacation destination. The state offers
history and art in its capital city of Providence, music and
excitement in Newport, spectacular and pristine scenery on Block
Island, and quiet, family-oriented beach communities along the
South County shoreline. By KAREN NELIS.
</P>
<P>
   FOOD (``d'' category)
</P>
<P>
   TV-FOOD-SHOWS (Lafayette, Calif.) _ There are too many TV
cooking shows. Now if every one of these offered useful tips on
good stuff I can cook, or better ways to cook what I now serve, I'd
say go for it. But the show-biz virus has infected the entire
system, the end result being culinary razzle-dazzle signifying
little besides how complicated and artsy-crafty a noble profession
can get. By KEN ALEXANDER.
</P>
<P>
