</P>
<P>
   MORSE-COLUMN (San Francisco) _ As a typical Bud-swilling
American male, I didn't think any woman could get me to put down
our culture's sacred phallic symbol, the TV remote control. It took
11 women to get me to stop pushing those buttons, but they did it,
and it'll happen again on Saturday. Two-thirds of the TV audience
for women's World Cup soccer has been men, and the reason is
simple: Women's soccer is a great sport, and translates well to TV.
The couch criterion is the ultimate male test for any sport. By ROB
MORSE.
