   &QL;  PA Contract Awards States News Service Washington, July 9 --
Fraccaro Industries Inc. of Boyerton won a $83,720 contract from
the Navy in Philadelphia for aircraft components.
</P>
<P>
   Klinge Corp. of York won a $184,015 contract from Camp Pendleton
in Virginia Beach for refrigerated containers.
</P>
<P>
   Ametek Inc. of Sellersville won a $180,150 contract from the
Defense Supply Center in Columbus, Ohio, for electrical components.
</P>
<P>
   Sunshine Scientific Instrument Inc. of Philadelphia won a
$92,655 contract from the Defense Supply Center in Columbus, Ohio,
for lab equipment.
</P>
<P>
   Laminated Glass Corp. of Telford won a $87,406 contract from the
Defense General Supply Center in Richmond, Va., for glass.
</P>
<P>
   Boeing Helicopter of Philadelphia won a $71,625 contract from
the Army at the Redstone Arsenal in Alabama for aircraft
components.
</P>
<P>
   United Defense LP of York won a $80,864 contract from the Army
in Warren, Mich., for ground effect vehicles.
</P>
<P>
   United Defense LP of York won a $928,000 contract from the Army
in Warren, Mich., for ground effect vehicles.
</P>
