<DOCNO> NYT19990709.0072 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-09 12:16 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A4295 &Cx1f; tdt-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-ALLSTAR-BUDGET-BOS &LR;      07-09 0292
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ALLSTAR-BUDGET-BOS </SLUG>
  
 For IMMEDIATE Release   
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move the following 1999 All-Star Game
stories today for use by NYTimes News Service clients. All stories
will bear the BOS designator and move under the Sports (s) category
code.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions, contact the NYTimes News Service desk at The
Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of graphics
or photos please call 212 556-4204 or -1927.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BBA-ALLST-EVENT (Boston) _ This used to be just a game. Now it's
a mega-celebration of the game of baseball -- and a mega-money
event. By Gregg Krupa. 1750 words.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-ALLST-YAZ (Boston) _ Carl Yastrzemski appeared in 14
All-Star Games. Ever a presence, Yaz wasn't exactly a good luck
charm for the American League, which lost 16 of the 18 games to
which he was invited. By Dan Shaughnessy. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-ALLST-NEGRO (Boston) _ The story of the Negro Leagues is as
much about race relations in this nation as it is about baseball.
By Larry Whiteside. 1600 words.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-ALLST-HALL (Boston) _ Ted Spencer's love for the game, plus
his position as curator of the Baseball Hall of Fame, makes him a
virtual baseball encyclopedia. By Michael Smith. 600 words.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-ALLST-CARLTON (Boston) _ Steve Carlton got to hit against
his digital self in 1996, and though the situation may not have
been as tense or as exciting as a real at-bat, he nonetheless got a
kick out of the experience. By Michael Smith. 965 words.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-TV-ALLSTAR (Boston) _ Anytime a television producer can
legitimately claim a game is not really a game but rather a
``show,'' then get ready for a veritable bonanza of programming. By
Howard Manly. 550 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The Boston Globe &LR;  &QC;
</P>
