<SLUG> BC-GAY-MURDERS-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TWO MEN CHARGED IN DEATHS OF GAY COUPLE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By RAY DELGADO  
 c.1999 San Francisco Examiner  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO _ Two brothers who are believed to be white
supremacists were arrested Thursday in connection with the shooting
deaths of a gay couple outside their rural Northern California
home.
</P>
<P>
   Benjamin Matthew Williams, 31, and James Tyler Williams, 29, are
accused of killing Gary Matson, 50, and Winfield Scott Mowder, 40,
the Shasta County Sheriff's Department said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
   The bodies of Matson and Mowder were found early Thursday in the
mobile home they shared on a five-acre plot in Happy Valley, a
community about 15 miles southwest of Redding.
</P>
<P>
   There was no obvious sign of forced entry and nothing of value
inside the home appeared to be missing, the authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   Matson's car _ a copper-colored, four-door 1987 Toyota Tercel
station wagon _ had been abandoned a day earlier.
</P>
<P>
   The deputies said in a press release that evidence in the car,
along with leads they already had, led investigators to identify
the Williams brothers as suspects.
</P>
<P>
   Deputies found ``information and literature'' in the home of the
two brothers that suggests they subscribed to racist beliefs,
according to a statement from the Sheriff's Department.
</P>
</TEXT>
