</P>
<P>
   &QR;  June 15 _ Eight children are reported sick in Kortrijk,
Belgium. Luxembourg bans Coca-Cola products. France closes a
bottling plant in Dunkirk. The Netherlands bans Coca-Cola products
shipped through Belgium.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  June 16 _ Germany bans Coca-Cola produced at the Dunkirk
plant. Coca-Cola issues its first apology to European consumers.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  June 18 _ M. Douglas Ivester, the chairman of Coca-Cola,
arrives in Belgium to personally oversee management of the crisis.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  June 22 _ Coca-Cola apologizes to Belgian consumers in
