<P>
   WOMEN-WORKPLACE _ Catalyst, an organization that promotes the
advancement of women, will release a study Tuesday that minority
women have an even tougher time advancing in management than women
overall. Instead of facing a 'glass ceiling,' minority women see
what they call a 'concrete ceiling.'' (McNoughton, Cox News
Service)
</P>
<P>
   DELTA-COMPUTERS _ ATLANTA _Delta Air Lines is installing
computer technology that it says will speed the process of getting
passengers onto its planes. It's part of the carrier's plans to
improve customer service. (Thurston, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   BELL-LAWSUIT _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Southwestern Bell Telephone Co.
allegedly owes its customers millions of dollars in refunds because
since 1991 it improperly collected a surcharge on monthly bills to
pay its municipal franchise fees, according to a recent lawsuit.
(Hight, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED
