<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-09 19:20 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A4851 &Cx1f; ttg-z
u a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BROWN-COMPUTER-COLUMN     07-09 0640
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BROWN-COMPUTER-COLUMN-NYTR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SWAPPING BUSINESS CONTACTS ON THE WEB  
 LEGAL RESOURCES ON THE WEB 
</HEADLINE>
  (EDS: (AT) in the e-mail address at the end of the article should
be replaced with the typographic symbol.) 
(js) 
 By LONNIE BROWN   
 Lakeland (Fla.) Ledger   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Web has become many things, and one of the things it has
become is a way to share business information quickly and easily.
Well, easier than swapping business cards.
</P>
<P>
   That's somewhat the concept behind ZCentral (www.zcentral.com).
The Web site offers free ``Z numbers'' so users can establish their
names and accounts. Once that's done, individuals can post their
business contact information: name, title, home and office
addresses and telephone numbers, hobbies and other information.
</P>
<P>
   But ZCentral does this just a little differently than other
sites. Users can restrict what information is shown to visitors to
the site. You might reveal only your name, occupation and hometown
in your posting. If a visitor wants to know more, he or she would
send e-mail asking for more information. And then those things
could be revealed on an individual basis.
</P>
<P>
   ``The power behind our site is our patented Zkey,'' said Darren
Jordan, spokesman for Zone Ventures, parent company of ZCentral.
``The Zkey allows members complete control over their profile on a
field-by-field, person-by-person basis.''
</P>
<P>
   It would be a handy place for business colleagues to post their
address books so only other workers would have access to those
address books. But what if you have hundreds of contacts to post?
</P>
<P>
   ``Zcentral will launch Version 3.0 in late August,'' said
Jordan. ``It will incorporate sync software so Zcentral may be used
in conjunction with all hand-held personal information managers,
including the new Palm VII and applications such as Microsoft's
Outlook.''
</P>
<P>
   What if you don't have a computer handy but need to use the
address book?
</P>
<P>
   ``Zcentral will also provide telephonic access to members for
off-Web use,'' he added.
</P>
<P>
   The site also provides its members with a calendar that can be
set for three different levels of access. There's a box for e-mail,
and conference-room capabilities are provided through AT&AMP;T's
Click2Dial. Users also are given 20 megabytes of storage space for
documents and file sharing.
</P>
<P>
   Sign-up is free. For information: www.zcentral.com.
</P>
<P>
   LEGAL RESOURCE ON THE WEB
</P>
<P>
   A few weeks ago, I wrote about self-help software that can
assist readers who need information about legal issues or may want
to hire an attorney.
</P>
<P>
   Lawoffice.com is a legal portal for businesses, professionals
and consumers. It's run by West Group, a prominent provider of
legal information. Although not a self-help site, it does offer
information about the law and the Web's largest directory of
attorneys, with more than 1 million listed.
</P>
<P>
   ``An extensive database of materials covers more than 400 legal
topics,'' said Molly Ready, spokeswoman for West Group. ``These
subjects include commercial, taxation, bankruptcy, real estate and
intellectual property law, as well as consumer-related issues like
estate planning, health, family and employment law.''
</P>
<P>
   The site also contains tips on which questions to ask before
hiring an attorney to make sure that person is suited for the task.
</P>
<P>
   There also is a dictionary of common legal terms, links to
relevant publications, and Web sites arranged by legal topic and
jurisdiction.
</P>
<P>
   The site has been recognized as one of The 50 Most Incredibly
Useful Sites by Yahoo!Internet Life, as well as The Best Place to
Find a Lawyer by PC World magazine. Fortune magazine lists it as
the ``grandpa of legal sites.''
</P>
<P>
   (Lonnie Brown is associate editor of The Ledger in Lakeland,
Fla. He can be reached by e-mail at LonnieB001(AT)aol.com.)
</P>
</TEXT>
