currency, it has become a source of anxiety. In a slide that has
surprised most economists, the euro has steadily declined against
the dollar from nearly $1.18 at its introduction on Jan. 4 to just
above $1.01 by the end of Friday. Global investors have begun
demanding a risk premium when buying euro-denominated bonds. By
