University, which participated in the study, reported a similar
flood of calls. The Mayo Clinic in Rochester, Minn., which
announced its own study of the scans a few weeks ago, received more
than 3,000 phone calls within a few days. By Denise Grady.
(Scheduled to move by 8:15 p.m. ET in ``a'' news file.)
