<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR SATURDAY, JULY 10
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Saturday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-SCI-LUNG-SCAN-NYT (moved on Thursday, July 8)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, July 8,
about the use of CAT scans to detect lung cancer referred
incorrectly at one point to steps taken when tumors are detected.
Some, but not all, are removed immediately. Others are monitored
and removed only if they grow.
</P>
<P>
   BC-CIR-GOLF-WEBSITES-NYT (moved on Wenesday, June 23)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wenesday, June 23,
about golfing sites on the World Wide Web misstated the ownership
of -pgatour.com. It is run by the PGA Tour, not the Professional
Golfers Association. A screen illustration with the article was
published in error. It was from www.globalgolf.com, not
www.globalgolfguide.com.
</P>
<P>
   BC-DIGICOM-COLUMN-NYT (moved on Sunday, July 4)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, July 4,
about efforts to foster on-line discussion groups referred
incorrectly to ``American Love Story,'' a PBS documentary that will
be the focus of on-line discussions produced in September by Web
Lab, a nonprofit group. The documentary is not part of the series
``P.O.V.''; it will have 10 episodes running over 5 evenings, not 5
episodes. Personal anecdotes for the discussion are being gathered
on the PBS Web site at www.pbs.org, not on Web Lab's site.
</P>
</TEXT>
