<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following for
clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of Saturday, July
10 and thereafter. If you have any questions, please call Bob
Schenet at (206) 448-8037.
</P>
<P>
   GORE (Seattle) _ A relentlessly serious Vice President Al Gore
uses two Seattle speeches to defend affirmative action, call for
removal of foreign countries' trade barriers, and pledge to assure
that Americans of all backgrounds and means get access to the
Internet. Gore comes loaded with statistics and specifics as he
addressed the UNITY '99 minority journalists conference and a
Washington Council on International Trade luncheon.
</P>
<P>
   By Joel Connelly. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   SOC-VECSEY-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ Column on final of women's
World Cup tournament.
</P>
<P>
   By Laura Vecsey. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BBO-MARINERS (Los Angeles) _ Seattle Mariners travel to Los
Angeles Dodgers.
</P>
<P>
   By Dan Raley. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
