is accompanied by his lawyer Marvyn Kornberg while leaving federal
court in February 1998. Government prosecutors, ending a lengthy
investigation of the New York Police Department initiated by the
Louima case, have told the Giuliani administration that they have
amassed evidence of system-wide problems in the department's
handling of police brutality complaints, and are seeking reforms,
officials said on Friday. (Steve Berman/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT16) PEC, Yugoslavia -- July 9, 1999 -- KOSOVO-2, 07-09 -- A
Kosovo Albanian cycling past the rubble of buildings in Pec. A
report showed that 40 to 45 percent of the houses in Pec were
destroyed in the war. (Tyler Hicks/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT15) UNDATED -- July 9, 1999 -- FRENCH-STYLE-2-HNS, 07-09 --
French design houses, such as Chanel, credit much of their success
to the fact that their fashions appeal as much to the men who
admire them as the women who wear them. The French have almost
institutionalized their style. So confident are they that names
such as Coco Chanel, Christian Dior, Givenchy, Herms and Louis
Vuitton can exist almost in perpetuity that those houses now have
designers who are German, British, Belgian or American. (Buster
Dean/Houston Chronicle Photo) LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT14) UNDATED -- July 9, 1999 -- FRENCH-STYLE-1-HNS, 07-09 --
French women know the power of well-respected fashion houses, such
as the venerable Hermes, where designer Martin Margiella uses only
top-quality fabrics. The French have almost institutionalized their
style. So confident are they that names such as Coco Chanel,
Christian Dior, Givenchy, Herms and Louis Vuitton can exist almost
in perpetuity that those houses now have designers who are German,
British, Belgian or American. (Buster Dean/Houston Chronicle Photo)
