separated by more than a generation but connected by a shared view
of the world. Ogletree, in a final tribute that is something like
one man completing another's last sentence, is finishing his
friend's incomplete books and articles. The partnership offers a
picture of one strand of modern black legal thought. (Jared
Leeds/New York Times Photo)
