<SLUG> BC-OBIT-FARMER-UPDATE-NYT </SLUG>
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The New York Times is adding the James Farmer obit to tomorrow's
front page. The abridged version of the obituary
(BC-OBIT-FARMER-ABRIDGED-NYT) has moved in national ``a'' news
file. The full-length version _ 3,200 words _ is scheduled to move
by midnight ET.
</P>
<P>
   OBIT-FARMER (Undated) _ James Farmer, a principal founder of the
Congress of Racial Equality and the last survivor of the ``Big
Four'' who shaped the civil-rights struggle in the United States in
the mid-1950s and '60s, died Friday at age 79. He lived in
Fredericksburg, Va.
</P>
</TEXT>
